    "en": {
      "title": "I don't know about non-resumption of Palali airport operations: Bandula",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Cabinet Spokesperson Bandula Gunawardena said that although it was reported that the activities of Palali Airport would be resumed, he was not aware of their non-operation on the specified day.",
        "Therefore, in this regard, he informed the Minister responsible for the matter, Nimal Siripala de Silva, to inform the media.",
        "It was announced in a cabinet resolution last week that the government has decided to resume the operations of Palali International Airport from July 1st.",
        "International operations of Palali Airport started on 11th November 2019 by confirming basic international regulatory requirements.",
        "However, due to the Covid-19 pandemic, its activities have been temporarily postponed until March 15, 2020.",
        "Internationally and domestically established airlines have now submitted requests to operate charter flights and scheduled flights from that airport to the South Indian airport.",
        "Accordingly, last week, the Cabinet approved the idea presented by the Minister of Ports and Air Transport Services regarding the commencement of international operations of Balali International Airport from July 1st.",
        "It is noteworthy that when asked about this by a journalist at the press conference announcing the cabinet decisions held in this situation, the minister replied in this way."
      ],
